{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS/MOCK-HIDE: a mocked loader/import path can miss real top-level module side effects. The failure boundary is manifest validation wired to real plugin discovery/import behavior. No external network/subprocess is required, so System is unnecessary.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one invalid plugin (e.g., missing `name`) whose entry module has a top-level side effect (writes a sentinel file). Run the real loader against that directory. Assert: loader reports manifest validation error for that plugin, sentinel side effect is absent, and no `onLoad` for that plugin ran.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: dependency graph + actual loader orchestration across multiple plugin modules is the failure boundary. A pure unit test of topological sort can miss wiring bugs between resolution and hook invocation.","test_description":"Create real plugin packages in a temp directory: `B` (no deps) and `A` (depends on `B`). Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared log file. Run loader and assert log order is `[\"B\",\"A\"]`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-HIDE: testing cycle detection function alone can miss real behavior that neither plugin is imported/initialized. Need real manifests plus loader execution path to verify both error reporting and suppression of loads.","test_description":"Create plugins `A` and `B` with mutual dependencies and top-level/module/onLoad side-effect sentinels. Run loader. Assert: cycle error includes both plugin names, no sentinel indicating import/onLoad for either plugin exists.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"REAL-INFRA (local module system): correctness depends on Node module import execution order (top-level code before exported hook call). In-process mocks can hide ordering issues between import and hook invocation.","test_description":"Create one plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.__pluginInitialized = true` at top level and whose `onLoad` throws if that flag is not set. Run loader and assert no throw from ordering violation and recorded sequence shows module top-level side effect before `onLoad` marker.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: continuation/skip behavior spans dependency resolution, error handling, and iterative hook execution across multiple plugins. Unit tests of try/catch logic alone can miss real dependency filtering and load progression.","test_description":"Create plugins: `X` (throws in `onLoad`), `Y` (independent), `Z` (depends on `X`), and `W` (independent). Run loader. Assert: `X` failure is reported; `Y` and `W` `onLoad` markers exist; `Z` `onLoad` marker does not; loader completes without aborting remaining independent plugins.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
